he first part presents methods and techniques for collecting and analyzing requirements for the development of a suitable data model. The basics of database systems are covered in the second part using the query language SQL and transaction management. The book concludes with a discussion of data warehouses and NoSQL databases.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aDatenbanken. 4aDatenmodell. 4aWirtschaftsinformatik. 7aCOMPUTERS / Computer Science.2bisacsh  aDatabases.  abusiness informatics.  adata model.1 aPernul, Günther, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Physical Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637212oZDB-23-GPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Computer Science 2014z9783110369625oZDB-23-DEI0 cEPUBz97834869897000 cprintz978348672141640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978348678129840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783486781298423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783486781298/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEIb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-GPSc2000d2014